  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantitative Researcher",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a <strong>Quantitative Researcher </strong>to provide research support for trading activities in <strong>energy-related futures and physical markets</strong>, with a focus on <strong>crude oil and refined products</strong>.</p><p>This role emphasizes the integration of research and practical application, leveraging <strong>quantitative analysis, machine learning, and AI tools</strong> to assist the trading team in market analysis, strategy validation, and decision-making.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct quantitative research on energy futures and physical markets (price spreads, term structure, seasonality, volatility, etc.).</li><li>Analyze market data using statistical methods and machine learning models.</li><li>Develop market indicators, produce research reports, and build analytical tools to support trading decisions.</li><li>Apply large language models (LLMs) to assist in research and analysis; able to construct and utilize simple <strong>prompt-based workflows, agents, or pipelines</strong> for internal analytical tasks.</li><li>Clearly present research findings to the trading team and effectively incorporate their feedback.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>A degree in a quantitative or technical field such as: Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Physics or other related STEM disciplines.</li><li>Solid foundation in statistics and data analysis.</li><li>Proficient in <strong>Python</strong> for research and data analysis.</li><li>Familiar with <strong>Large Language Models and related AI tools</strong>, with an understanding of prompt engineering and agent fundamentals.</li><li>Prior internship, project experience or work experience in <strong>finance, trading and commodities</strong> is preferred.</li><li>Strong interest in futures, derivatives and commodity markets.</li><li>Collaborative, able to work closely with traders and align research with practical trading needs.</li><li>Result-oriented with strong attention to detail.</li><li>Comfortable working in a fast paced trading environment.</li></ul>",
